# Rust

- Prefer `Result` and `Option`; avoid `unwrap`/`expect` in library code without strong justification.
- Minimize `unsafe`; document invariants when `unsafe` is required.
- Use `clippy` and `fmt` per project; keep public API documented with `///`.
- Prefer iterators over manual indexing when it improves clarity and safety.
- Structure modules to keep visibility minimal (`pub(crate)` etc.).
